2d array 
consist of rows and columns 

syntax - int[][] arr = new int[3][5]

while declaring array we have to declare no of rows and clumns numbers are optional
each row will act as a individual array 

import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int[][] arr = new int[3][7];
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        for (int i =0 ; i<arr.length;i++){
            for (int j=0 ; j<arr[0].length;j++){
                System.out.println("Enter the"+i+j+"value");
                arr[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
            }
        }
        for (int i =0 ; i<arr.length;i++){
            for (int j=0 ; j<arr[0].length;j++){
                System.out.print(arr[i][j]);
                
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }  
